    • Method Detail

      • attributesUpdated

        void attributesUpdated​(HlaPhysicalInterface physicalInterface,
                       java.util.Set<HlaPhysicalInterfaceAttributes.Attribute> attributes,
                       HlaTimeStamp timeStamp,
                       HlaLogicalTime logicalTime)
        This method is called when a HLA reflectAttributeValueUpdate is received for an remote object, or a set of attributes is updated on a local object.
        Parameters:
        physicalInterface - The physicalInterface which this update corresponds to.
        attributes - The set of attributes that are updated.
        timeStamp - The time when the update was initiated.
        logicalTime - The logical time when the update was initiated.
